Benin – Dr Harrison Osasogie, a medical practitioner at Faith Clinic Benin, says regular intake of fruits helps in the reduction of chronic diseases. Osasogie made this known in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Benin on Sunday. “Eating foods such as fruits that are lower in calories per cup instead of some other higher-calorie foods may be useful in helping to lower calorie intake. “It also reduces risk of heart disease, including heart attack and stroke. “Eating of foods regularly is better than soft drinks, because it protects against certain types of cancers. “It can help increase intake of fiber and potassium which are important nutrients. “Some fruit sources of potassium include bananas, prunes and prune juice, dried peaches and apricots, cantaloupe, honeydew melon and orange juice. Buhari will not implement anti-poor policies, says BMO “Fruits are very important to the body. It makes you younger and make your skin glow, ’’he said. Osasogie said that fruits provided nutrients vital for health and maintenance of the body. According to him, most fruits are naturally low in fat, sodium, and calories and have no cholesterol. He advised the general public to eat fruits regularly, saying that fruits were sources of many essential nutrients that were under-consumed, including potassium, dietary fiber, vitamin C and Folate (folic acid). (NAN)